import os
import numpy as np
from PIL import Image

print("1. (Feature Extraction)")
print("Used these websites as help for this section:")
print("https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/python-pil-image-resize-method/")
print("https://www.statology.org/numpy-normalize-between-0-and-1/")
print("https://stackoverflow.com/questions/70783357/how-do-i-normalize-the-pixel-value-of-an-image-to-01")
print("Resizing the cropped images to 224x224\n")

cropped_images = r'C:\Users\colin\Downloads\Data Mining 1 - Programming Assignment 1\Cropped'
new_cropped_images = r'C:\Users\colin\Downloads\Data Mining 1 - Programming Assignment 1\NewCropped'
crop_dimensions = (224, 224)

if not os.path.exists(new_cropped_images):
    os.makedirs(new_cropped_images)

for class_name in os.listdir(cropped_images):
    class_path = os.path.join(cropped_images, class_name)
    new_class_path = os.path.join(new_cropped_images, class_name)
    
    if not os.path.exists(new_class_path):
        os.makedirs(new_class_path)

    for image_name in os.listdir(class_path):
        image_path = os.path.join(class_path, image_name)
        new_image_path = os.path.join(new_class_path, image_name)
        with Image.open(image_path) as img:
            resized_image = img.resize(crop_dimensions, Image.LANCZOS) 
            array_of_images = np.array(resized_image)  
            normalized_images = array_of_images / 255  
            normalized_image = Image.fromarray((normalized_images * 255).astype(np.uint8))
            normalized_image.save(new_image_path)

# collapse-hide

##### DATASET


class ImageData(Dataset):
    # init
    def __init__(self, data, directory, transform):
        self.data = data
        self.directory = directory
        self.transform = transform

    # length
    def __len__(self):
        return len(self.data)

    # get item
    def __getitem__(self, idx):
        # import
        image = cv2.imread(
            os.path.join(self.directory, self.data.iloc[idx]["image_id"])
        )
        image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)

        # augmentations
        image = self.transform(image=image)["image"]

        return image

##### HELPER FUNCTION FOR FEATURE EXTRACTION


def get_features(name):
    def hook(model, input, output):
        features[name] = output.detach()

    return hook
In[6]:
##### REGISTER HOOK

model.global_pool.register_forward_hook(get_features("feats"))

##### FEATURE EXTRACTION LOOP

# Placeholder
PREDS = []
FEATS = []

# Placeholder for batch features
features = {}

# Loop through batches
for idx, inputs in enumerate(data_loader):
    # move to device
    inputs = inputs.to(device)

    # forward pass [with feature extraction]
    preds = model(inputs)

    # add feats and preds to lists
    PREDS.append(preds.detach().cpu().numpy())
    FEATS.append(features["feats"].cpu().numpy())

    # early stop
    if idx == 9:
        break

print("Had to convert list to a numpy array so that I can perform the dimensionality reduction")
converted_features = np.concatenate(FEATS, axis=0)

plt.scatter(reduced_dimensionality[:, 0], reduced_dimensionality[:, 1], c=single_link_labels, cmap='brg')
plt.title('Single link (MIN) Agglomerative clustering with K=4 and linkage = single')

plt.ylabel("Component 2")
plt.show()
